The paper deals with transfer learning in machine comprehension, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a novel two-stage synthesis network, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with document understanding and question answering, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
